# BROWSER-recommend.md - Substack Publication Recommendation Patterns

**Profile: `{{browser_profile}}`** — pass on EVERY browser call.

## Overview

Recommendations are outgoing endorsements of other Substack publications. They appear on your profile and in recommendation digests to subscribers. When you recommend someone, they get notified and may reciprocate — this is the #1 organic subscriber growth mechanism on Substack.

**Dashboard URL:** `https://{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/recommendations`

---

## SS 1. Check Existing Recommendations

Navigate to the recommendations dashboard to see what's already recommended.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    // Extract outgoing recommendations list
    var text = document.body.innerText;
    var hasOutgoing = text.includes('Outgoing recommendations');
    // Find all recommendation rows - they appear between "Outgoing recommendations" and "Suggested"
    var rows = [];
    var allBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var activeBtns = allBtns.filter(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Active');
    // Each Active button corresponds to one recommendation
    for (var btn of activeBtns) {
      var row = btn.closest('[class*=row]') || btn.parentElement.parentElement;
      if (row) {
        var rowText = row.innerText.replace(/\\n/g, ' | ').slice(0, 100);
        rows.push(rowText);
      }
    }
    // Also get suggested publications
    var recBtns = allBtns.filter(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Recommend');
    var suggested = recBtns.map(b => {
      var parent = b.parentElement;
      return parent ? parent.innerText.replace(/\\n/g, ' ').slice(0, 80) : '';
    });
    return { existing: rows, suggestedCount: suggested.length, suggested: suggested };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

