## SS 3. Recommend from Suggested List

Simpler flow — click the "Recommend" button next to a suggested publication. No search needed, but no reason/blurb is added.

🚨 **Prefer SS 2 (Add recommendation) over SS 3** — the reason/blurb adds credibility and shows up for subscribers. Only use SS 3 as fallback if SS 2 search fails to find the publication.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var recBtns = btns.filter(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Recommend');
    // Match by nearby text (publication name in parent)
    var target = recBtns.find(b => {
      var parent = b.parentElement;
      return parent && parent.innerText.toLowerCase().includes(${JSON.stringify(publicationName.toLowerCase())});
    });
    if (!target) return { error: 'publication not in suggested list' };
    target.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    var pageText = document.body.innerText;
    var verified = pageText.includes('Recommendation added');
    return { submitted: true, verified: verified };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

